## THE CROSS-REFERENCE PROTOCOL

D.R.D cross-referencing operates across three simultaneous channels:

```
CHANNEL 1 — SOURCE TRIANGULATION
The same claim is tested against multiple independent sources.
When three or more independent streams — from different
traditions, disciplines, or time periods — point to the same
conclusion, that convergence carries significant weight.
A single source, no matter how compelling, remains provisional.

CHANNEL 2 — CODEX ALIGNMENT
All research is cross-referenced against the Pandora Codex.
Where findings align with existing Codex doctrine, they
strengthen it. Where findings challenge or expand it,
both are noted. The Codex is living doctrine —
it grows as D.R.D refines it.

CHANNEL 3 — PATTERN RECOGNITION
Patterns that appear across unrelated fields simultaneously
are noted as meaningful. A concept appearing in ancient texts,
modern physics, and indigenous oral tradition pointing to the
same underlying principle is worth investigating carefully
rather than dismissing as coincidence.
```

