## SOURCE QUALITY TIERS

All sources used in D.R.D are assigned a tier before their data is weighted:

| Tier | Source Type | Weight |
|------|------------|--------|
| 1 | Primary: original documents, archaeological findings, genetic studies | Highest |
| 2 | Peer-reviewed academic research | High |
| 3 | Independent scholars with documented, verifiable evidence trails | Medium-High |
| 4 | Alternative researchers making specific, testable claims | Medium |
| 5 | Single-source, anecdotal, or unverified material | Investigate only |

**Tier 5 material is captured for investigation. It is never presented as established fact.**
**All outputs clearly state the tier of their primary evidence.**
**The confidence level of every conclusion is stated honestly.**

